external_knowledge:
- "threshold of the ordinary" refers to the unit cost greater than $20;
- "names and traits of the treasures" refers to product_name, description, category_name, etc.;
- "banners" metaphorically refers to brand names;
- "narratives of their categories" refers to category descriptions;
- "whispers of their variations" refers to variation_name and variation_value;
- "silence of their stockpiles" refers to quantity in stock;
- "echoes of their storerooms" refers to the inventory location;
- "shadows of their orders" refers to order_date and the order's unit price and discount;
- "echoes of their buyers" refers to customer_name and email;
- "depths of their discounts" refers to the discount applied.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT c.customer_name, c.email, c.phone_number
FROM orders AS o
INNER JOIN customers AS c ON o.customer_id = c.customer_id;

SELECT total_cost 
FROM orders 
WHERE order_id = 1;

SELECT p.product_name, p.description, s.supplier_name
FROM products p
LEFT JOIN suppliers s ON p.supplier_id = s.supplier_id;
